WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:03.273
Narrator:
In New York City war on crime,

00:03.303 --> 00:06.580
the worst criminal offenders
are pursued by the detectives

00:06.607 --> 00:08.280
of the Major Case Squad.

00:08.308 --> 00:10.288
These are their stories.

00:12.079 --> 00:14.753
( beeping )

00:14.781 --> 00:17.284
- Get a crash cart, stat!
- All right, I'm on it.

00:17.317 --> 00:20.821
Code Blue on Ward 11-B, north block, bed 5!

00:20.854 --> 00:22.629
- Any peripheral pulses?
- No.

00:22.656 --> 00:25.660
V-fib. She has a shockable rhythm.

00:25.692 --> 00:27.865
- Start at 200 joules.
- Charging to 200.

00:27.895 --> 00:29.704
- Clean
- ( thumps )

00:29.730 --> 00:32.904
Alton on post on 11-B, north block.

00:32.933 --> 00:34.606
(sighs)

00:34.635 --> 00:37.343
Better catch your breath,
or we'll need the crash cart for you.

00:37.371 --> 00:39.715
I am so glad I was there
when Mrs. Taylor coded.

00:39.740 --> 00:41.447
Not as glad as she is, I bet.

00:41.475 --> 00:43.648
She's going to be fine.
Dr. Gardetta's going

00:43.677 --> 00:45.953
to keep her sedated with Valium.
Good work, Colleen.

00:45.979 --> 00:47.981
- Looks like you're a hero.
- No, I'm not.

00:48.015 --> 00:49.722
Did you see in the papers?

00:49.750 --> 00:52.526
They're having a book fair
on Third Avenue this Saturday.

00:52.553 --> 00:54.692
Yeah? Well, I'm, you know,

00:54.721 --> 00:56.860
headed out to Sheepshead Bay,
check on my folks.

00:56.890 --> 00:59.268
I'll see you later.

01:02.396 --> 01:06.640
Maintenance to cafeteria annex.
Maintenance to cafeteria annex.

01:06.667 --> 01:08.738
Will you come see our new goldfish, Grandma?

01:08.769 --> 01:11.249
Of course, honey.

01:11.271 --> 01:13.444
Ma, are you all right?

01:13.473 --> 01:15.578
I heard they had an emergency.

01:15.609 --> 01:18.920
Mrs. Taylor. She had a little
thing with her heart.

01:18.946 --> 01:21.256
Okay, kids, let's let Grandma go to sleep.

01:21.281 --> 01:24.194
Goodbye, Grandma. We love you.

01:25.218 --> 01:28.495
I don't know what I would've done if--

01:28.522 --> 01:30.195
Stop staring.

01:31.792 --> 01:33.328
How's your chest feel?

01:33.360 --> 01:36.830
It's better. The doctor says
my lung is healing fine.

01:36.863 --> 01:39.901
I'm going to need some help at
home when they let me out of here.

01:39.933 --> 01:41.776
We'll get one of those home nurses.

01:41.802 --> 01:45.443
- Medicare won't pay for that.
- How do you know that?

01:45.472 --> 01:46.917
You're always so negative.

01:46.940 --> 01:49.443
Can't you come stay with me for a while?

01:49.476 --> 01:52.855
Ma, I've fed your cat and watered
your plants for two weeks already.

01:54.181 --> 01:56.218
Time for your pills.

01:56.249 --> 01:58.661
No, I just want to sleep.

01:58.685 --> 02:01.291
It's all right, dear, you can
take them when you wake up.

02:05.425 --> 02:09.339
Oh, I brought the paperwork
from Cutie Bear to sign.

02:11.365 --> 02:13.971
You know, I think of you

02:14.001 --> 02:17.141
in your apartment all by yourself.

02:17.170 --> 02:20.151
Lenny's things everywhere.

02:23.477 --> 02:26.583
And for the last time,
leave that poor woman alone.

